  "title": "Corporate Secretarial Assistant Manager (Professional Services Firm)",
  "description": "<p>An exciting opportunity has presented itself to join an established global professional services firm, specializing in trust and private wealth and servicing high net worth individuals.<br /><br />The role sits in a lean corporate secretarial department and works closely with related departments.<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities </strong><br />You will be responsible for handling regulatory filing, board meeting management (prepare agendas, draft minutes etc), and providing general advisory to clients. This is a high touch role involving high net worth clients, hence someone who exercises discretion would be valued.<br /><br />Someone who is meticulous, accurate and ensuring smooth flow in work processes would be suitable.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong><br />At least 4 years relevant experience in a professional services environment, ideally with exposure to private clients and/family offices.<br /><br />A resilient approach and strong commitment to client servicing is welcomed for this role.<br /><br /><strong>To Apply</strong><br />Interest and referral to co@kerryconsulting.com</p><p>Reg: R1544641 Lic: 16S8060</p>",
